                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine, by well-trained hand.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid red)</seg>
                        Possibly, the names ʾArsāni and Śarḍa Dǝngǝl written at the
                        upper margin of some fols. are the names of the scribes (za-ʾArsāni “of
                        ʾArsāni” on <locus target="#140r">140r</locus>, 149v, 150r, 161v, 162r, 175v;
                        za-Śarḍa Dǝngǝl “of Śarḍa Dǝngǝl” on <locus target="#176r">176r</locus>).
                        <date>Mid-17th century</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ክ/ክፍ</abbr> for <expan>ክፍል </expan> (10rb, 183va)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors and members of
                           their families; a few lines in the incipit page, alternating with black
                           lines; two initial lines of each section of the text; elements of the
                           punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; some words like kǝfl
                           (e.g., 186vb, 199rc, 207rb), fǝkkāre (e.g., fols. 205vb, 206vb, 207rb),
                           rabǝʿ (e.g., fols. 208va, 209rb, 209va).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
